-- Routed attestation observation merge — the present-row half of the apply.
--
-- NATIVE (2026-07-21, GH #565): the body lives in C (src/fold_route.c). The
-- write lane's probe already proved every row here EXISTS; the only job is
-- observation_count accumulation + last_observed_at advance, routed to the
-- LIST(type_id) -> HASH(subject_id) leaves the caller already knows.
--
-- History of the SQL forms this replaces (all measured, kept so nobody
-- re-tries them):
--  * naive UPDATE ... FROM unnest(ids): no partition key -> Append-scans EVERY
--    leaf per chunk (measured 2026-07-19 on the OMW seed: ~10s per 32k chunk
--    flat, ~9 minutes of a 19-minute step).
--  * plpgsql loop with the type in a VARIABLE: an UPDATE's target result
--    relations are opened and locked at PLAN time, and a variable plans
--    generically -- every call opened all ~1,600 leaves (measured 2026-07-21:
--    one 32k chunk at 93.8% CPU for 58 minutes, 10.2 GB relcache RSS, zero
--    rows updated).
--  * plpgsql temp table + per-type EXECUTE format(%L): correct pruning at
--    last -- but a fresh temp table + CREATE INDEX + ANALYZE per call, and a
--    full re-plan of a partitioned UPDATE per type per chunk, forever.
--
-- The native routing groups the batch by type in C and executes a
-- SESSION-CACHED prepared plan per type whose type_id is a LITERAL in the plan
-- text (HTAB of type -> SPI_keepplan'd plan in TopMemoryContext): LIST pruning
-- once per (backend, type) and reused across every chunk and every apply,
-- HASH pruning per row, no temp table, no ANALYZE, no re-plan.
--
-- Contract with the caller (NpgsqlWorkingSetApply) — unchanged:
--   * arrays are parallel and CLIENT-DEDUPED per call — one row per
--     attestation id (a duplicate id would double-apply the UPDATE);
--   * every id was probe-verified present under the apply advisory lock;
--   * rows arrive sorted by (type, subject, id) — partition-key order, so
--     cross-writer lock acquisition stays globally ordered; the router only
--     needs same-type rows ADJACENT and remains correct (merely one extra
--     plan execution) if they are not.
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION attestation_merge(
    p_ids      bytea[],
    p_types    bytea[],
    p_subjects bytea[],
    p_games    bigint[],
    p_ts       timestamptz[])
    RETURNS bigint
    AS 'MODULE_PATHNAME', 'pg_laplace_attestation_merge'
    LANGUAGE C VOLATILE;
